body:
I'm using glfw3.0.3. (using brew install glfw3). What's the best way to get glfw4 on a mac? And I wasn't calling the appropriate cleanup funcs in attempt to distill the bug to as minimal as possible.

With updated code:

```
#include <GLFW/glfw3.h>
#include <stdio.h>

void err(int error, const char* description)
{
  fprintf(stderr, "Error: %s\n", description);
}

int main(int argc, char **argv)
{
  glfwSetErrorCallback(err);
  glfwInit();
  glfwTerminate();
  return 0;
}
```

I get alternating behavior between:

```
Error: Cocoa: Failed to find NSScreen for CGDisplay `ɻ
a.out(32242,0x7fff7b8a0310) malloc: *** error for object 0x7fbbc9603f50: pointer being freed was not allocated
*** set a breakpoint in malloc_error_break to debug
Abort trap: 6
```

and 

```
Segmentation fault: 11
```

I'll quick look into updating my glfw (if you know a quick/easy way, I'd appreciate a link!) and get back to you. Thanks!
